# Registering Components to Registry

When adding components to the registry, follow these steps:

## 1. Prepare Component Code

- Use path aliases (`@/utils/cn`, `@/components/ui/badge`) instead of relative paths
- Ensure all dependencies are properly imported

## 2. Update Main Registry (`registry.json`)

Add entry with required fields:

```json
{
  "name": "component-name",
  "type": "registry:component",
  "title": "Component Title",
  "description": "Brief description of the component.",
  "dependencies": ["motion"],
  "registryDependencies": ["other-registry-component"],
  "files": [
    {
      "path": "src/components/component-name.tsx",
      "type": "registry:component",
      "target": "src/nhatcapdang/component-name.tsx"
    }
  ]
}
```

## 3. Create Public Registry File (`public/r/[name].json`)

Include full component content:

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://ui.shadcn.com/schema/registry-item.json",
  "name": "component-name",
  "type": "registry:component",
  "title": "Component Title",
  "description": "Description here",
  "dependencies": ["motion"],
  "files": [
    {
      "path": "src/components/component-name.tsx",
      "content": "// Full file content as escaped string",
      "type": "registry:component",
      "target": "src/nhatcapdang/component-name.tsx"
    }
  ]
}
```

## 4. Sync Public Registry

Copy updated `registry.json` content to `public/r/registry.json`.

## Key Notes

- Use `registryDependencies` for components that depend on other registry components
- Include `dependencies` for npm packages (e.g., `motion`)
- CSS-only styles use `cssVars` and `css` fields
